question: Is Keutel syndrome a common genetic disorder?
ideal_answer: No, Keutel syndrome (OMIM 245150) is a very rare syndrome

snippets.text: Keutel syndrome (OMIM 245150) is a very rare syndrome
Keutel syndrome is a rare autosomal-recessive condition characterized by abnormal cartilage calcification.
MGP-deficiency in humans leads to Keutel syndrome, a rare genetic disease hallmarked by abnormal soft tissue calcification.
